('{"formato":"iso_29110","proceso":"Project Management (PM) process","p_id":"6","p_proposito":"The purpose of the Project Management process is to establish and carry out in a systematic way the Tasks<br>of the software implementation project, which allows complying with the projectu2019s Objectives in the expected<br>quality, time and costs.","obj_nombre_2":"The Change Requests are addressed through their reception and analysis. Changes to software requirements are evaluated for cost, schedule and technical impact.","obj_nombre_1":"Progress of the project is monitored against the Project Plan and recorded in the Progress Status Record. Corrections to remediate problems and deviations from the plan are taken when project targets are not achieved. Closure of the project is performed to get the Customer acceptance documented in the Acceptance Record.","obj_nombre_0":"The Project Plan for the execution of the project is developed according to the Statement of Work and reviewed and accepted by the Customer. The Tasks and Resources necessary to complete the work are sized and estimated.","rol_2":"Tecnico","rol_abr_2":"TL","rol_1":"Project manager","rol_abr_1":"PM","rol_0":"Customer","rol_abr_0":"CUS","pent_nombre_2":"Change request","pent_fuente_2":"Customer","pent_nombre_1":"Soft config","pent_fuente_1":"Soft implement","pent_nombre_0":"Statement","pent_fuente_0":"Customer","psal_nombre_2":"Repositorio","psal_destino_2":"Soft implement","psal_nombre_1":"Acceptance record","psal_destino_1":"Organizacion","psal_nombre_0":"Project plan","psal_destino_0":"Soft implement","pint_nombre_2":"Meeting record","pint_nombre_1":"Correction register","pint_nombre_0":"Change request","actividad_0":"Project planning","tar_nombre_0_1":"Review the Statement of Work","tar_rol_0_1":"PM","tar_pent_0_1":"Statement of Work","tar_psal_0_1":"Statement of Work [reviewed]"}'),
('{"formato":"iso_12207","proceso":"Organizational Project-Enabling Processes","p_id":"6.2","proposito_0":"The purpose of the Life Cycle Model Management Process is to define, maintain, and assure availability of policies, life cycle processes, life cycle models, and procedures for use by the organization with respect to the scope of this International Standard. This process provides life cycle policies, processes, and procedures that are consistent with the organization''s objectives, that are defined, adapted, improved and maintained to support individual project needs within the context of the organization, and that are capable of being applied using effective, proven methods and tools.","resultado_num_0":"policies and procedures for the management and deployment of life cycle models and processes are provided;","resultado_num_3":"prioritized process improvements are implemented","resultado_num_2":"responsibility, accountability and authority for life cycle management are defined","resultado_num_1":"life cycle processes, models and procedures for use by the organization are defined, maintained and improved","act_0":"Process establishment","tarea_0_act_0":"The organization shall establish a suite of organizational processes for all software life cycle processes and life cycle models as they apply to its business activities. The processes and their application to specific cases shall be documented in the organization''s publications. As appropriate, a process control mechanism should be established to develop, monitor, control, and improve the process(es).","nota_tarea_0":"Establishing the process control mechanism includes the definition of responsibility, accountability and authority for life cycle management","act_1":"Process assessment","tarea_1_1":"The organization should develop, document and apply a process assessment procedure. Assessment records should be produced and maintained.","nota_tarea_1":"The organization shall plan and carry out reviews of the processes at appropriate intervals to ensure their continuing suitability and effectiveness in the light of assessment results","act_2":"Process improvement","tarea_2_2":"The organization shall effect such improvements to its processes as it determines to be necessary as a result of process assessment and review. Process documentation should be updated to reflect improvement in the organizational processes","tarea_3_2":"Historical, technical, and evaluation data should be collected and analyzed to gain an understanding of the strengths and weaknesses of the employed processes. These analyses should be used as feedback to improve these processes, to recommend changes in the direction of the projects (or subsequent projects), and to determine technology advancement needs.","tarea_4_2":"Quality cost data should be collected, maintained, and used to improve the organization''s processes as a management activity. These data shall serve the purpose of establishing the cost of both the prevention and resolution of problems and non-conformity in software products and services"}'),
